Reasoning: The paper deals with capacity-achieving schemes for MIMO broadcast channels, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. It also involves multiple users and network modulation, which suggests that it could also belong to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The use of space-time coding and the extension to other communication networks with MIMO links suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
